

---
const pageTitle = "Hero";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .topbar span {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 0 8px;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background:
          linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.94), rgba(245,245,245,0.94)),
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            to bottom,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 0px,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 4px
          );
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(6deg);
        width: 300px;
        height: 300px;
        opacity: 0.2;
        pointer-events: none;
        user-select: none;
        z-index: 0;
      }

      .symbol-bg svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        display: block;
      }

      .content-layer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 42px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 15px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        text-transform: lowercase;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
      }

      p { margin: 0 0 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px;
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #f3f3f3, #ebebeb);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 30px 0 14px;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        margin: 0 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      .content-layer p,
      .content-layer h1,
      .content-layer h2,
      .content-layer .subtitle,
      .content-layer .divider,
      .content-layer .quote,
      .content-layer .mini-links,
      .content-layer .footer-note {
        text-shadow: 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        h1 { font-size: 34px; }
        .symbol-bg {
          width: 210px;
          height: 210px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/">archetypes index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/archetypes/wise-old-man">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/archetypes/shadow-archetype">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none">
            <g stroke="#000000" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M110 66 L150 106 L190 66" />
              <path d="M150 106 L150 220" />
              <path d="M132 220 L168 220" />
              <path d="M120 234 L180 234" />
              <path d="M145 54 L150 34 L155 54" />

              <path d="M76 104 L120 148 L84 184" />
              <path d="M120 148 L214 242" />
              <path d="M72 188 L96 164" />
              <path d="M62 198 L106 154" />
              <path d="M64 92 L46 74 L82 86" />

              <circle cx="150" cy="150" r="56" />
              <path d="M118 150 C118 128, 132 114, 150 114 C168 114, 182 128, 182 150" />
              <path d="M126 166 C136 176, 164 176, 174 166" />
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>Hero</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">archetypes / will / journey / archive entry 001</p>

          <div class="divider">***</div>

          <p>
            The hero is the archetype of effort, direction, and confrontation.
            It emerges when a person begins to take life into their own hands,
            moving toward something rather than drifting.
          </p>

          <p>
            At first, the hero appears as strength and determination. It wants
            to overcome obstacles, define identity, and prove capability.
            It separates from dependency and begins to stand alone.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            the hero begins where passive existence ends.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">struggle and identity</h2>

          <p>
            The hero forms identity through challenge. Without resistance,
            there is no clear sense of self. Through effort, a person discovers
            what they can endure, what they value, and what they are willing to
            fight for.
          </p>

          <p>
            This is why early development often requires a heroic phase.
            Without it, the personality remains undefined and easily shaped
            by external forces.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">limits of the hero</h2>

          <p>
            The hero is necessary, but not complete. If held too tightly,
            it becomes rigid, prideful, and disconnected from deeper parts
            of the psyche.
          </p>

          <p>
            Eventually, the hero must confront what it cannot defeat —
            the shadow, the unconscious, and the limits of control.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/">back to archetypes index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/archetypes/shadow-archetype">continue to: shadow</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">
            this page is part of the hidden archive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>